sec.p:
In a report on why female chemistry PhDs in the United Kingdom leave academia, the following were listed among the reasons they did so:


Been uncomfortable with the culture of their research group (about working patterns, time and expectations and the level of competition between group members), especially where the culture was particularly “macho”;

Come to believe the competition for a permanent academic post was too fierce for them to compete successfully. (Newsome, 2008, p. 7)
